+{"parentUuid":"28a142ec-98f7-4f1b-99a6-a8f2e39f0e96","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/workspace","sessionId":"0daa0aae-caa7-44f1-a436-5ea716b7ea01","version":"2.1.63","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"partitioned-seeking-fox","type":"progress","data":{"message":{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RCbB9LV4PHA6CpufQbBKK2","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# T3: Full-Text Search Feature\n     2→\n     3→## Category\n     4→features/medium\n     5→\n     6→## Timeout\n     7→30 minutes\n     8→\n     9→## Description\n    10→An existing Express + SQLite note-taking API has CRUD endpoints for notes (title, body, tags, timestamps) and tag-based filtering. Add full-text search using SQLite FTS5.\n    11→\n    12→## Requirements\n    13→\n    14→### 1. Search Endpoint: `GET /notes/search?q=<query>`\n    15→- Full-text search across note titles and bodies using SQLite FTS5\n    16→- Results ranked by relevance (BM25 ranking)\n    17→- Snippet highlighting with `<mark>` tags around matched terms\n    18→- Quoted phrase support (e.g., `?q=\"exact phrase\"`)\n    19→- Pagination: 20 results per page, controlled by `?page=N` parameter\n    20→- Response format: `{ results: SearchResult[], total: number, page: number, perPage: number }`\n    21→- Returns 400 if `q` parameter is missing or empty\n    22→\n    23→### 2. Suggest Endpoint: `GET /notes/search/suggest?q=<prefix>`\n    24→- Autocomplete that returns up to 5 matching note titles\n    25→- Matches prefix against note content (title and body)\n    26→- Response format: `{ results: SuggestResult[] }`\n    27→- Returns 400 if `q` parameter is missing or empty\n    28→\n    29→### 3. FTS Index Synchronization\n    30→- FTS index must stay in sync when notes are created, updated, or deleted\n    31→- Use SQLite triggers or manual sync in the CRUD operations\n    32→\n    33→## Interfaces (already defined in `src/models.ts`)\n    34→\n    35→```ts\n    36→interface SearchResult {\n    37→  id: number;\n    38→  title: string;\n    39→  snippet: string;  // with <mark> highlighting\n    40→  rank: number;\n    41→}\n    42→\n    43→interface SuggestResult {\n    44→  id: number;\n    45→  title: string;\n    46→}\n    47→```\n    48→\n    49→## Existing Code\n    50→- `src/db.ts` - Database setup with `notes` table\n    51→- `src/models.ts` - TypeScript interfaces (SearchResult and SuggestResult already defined)\n    52→- `src/routes.ts` - CRUD routes for notes\n    53→- `src/errors.ts` - Error handling middleware\n    54→- `src/server.ts` - Express app setup\n    55→- `src/seed.ts` - Seed script with ~50 sample notes\n    56→\n    57→## Tests\n    58→- `tests/notes.test.ts` - 15 existing CRUD tests (must continue passing)\n    59→- `tests/search.test.ts` - 20 search tests (must pass after implementation)\n    60→\n    61→## Validation\n    62→```bash\n    63→npm test\n    64→```\n    65→All 35 tests must pass.\n    66→"}]},"uuid":"c129e5d0-44e8-4754-8c1c-1001db5a7c5d","timestamp":"2026-03-10T20:27:49.822Z"},"normalizedMessages":[],"type":"agent_progress","prompt":"","agentId":"a69653073fbcb5eaf"},"toolUseID":"agent_msg_01Jukp7WoUpUU935VnaFUYsk","parentToolUseID":"toolu_017US58y4C22M9vnrPvT1RVZ","uuid":"5e196d87-c850-47a0-b13a-8fe2dd4f126c","timestamp":"2026-03-10T20:27:49.832Z"}
+{"parentUuid":"e72f493f-34c0-4b6d-90c2-2cba706b7d9c","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/workspace","sessionId":"0daa0aae-caa7-44f1-a436-5ea716b7ea01","version":"2.1.63","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"partitioned-seeking-fox","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017US58y4C22M9vnrPvT1RVZ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a complete understanding of the codebase. Let me provide you with a comprehensive report.\n\n## Complete Codebase Analysis\n\n### Project Overview\nThis is a **Full-Text Search Feature** project for an Express + SQLite note-taking API. The task is to add FTS5 (Full-Text Search) capabilities including search, suggestions, and automatic index synchronization.\n\n---\n\n### 1. File Structure\n\n```\n/workspace\n├── package.json\n├── tsconfig.json\n├── vitest.config.ts\n├── TASK.md\n├── src/\n│   ├── db.ts\n│   ├── models.ts\n│   ├── routes.ts\n│   ├── errors.ts\n│   ├── server.ts\n│   └── seed.ts\n└── tests/\n    ├── notes.test.ts\n    └── search.test.ts\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. Dependencies (package.json)\n\n**Runtime Dependencies:**\n- `better-sqlite3` - ^11.0.0 (SQLite driver)\n- `express` - ^4.21.0 (Web framework)\n\n**Dev Dependencies:**\n- `typescript` - ^5.4.0\n- `vitest` - ^2.0.0 (Test runner)\n- `eslint` - ^8.56.0\n- `@typescript-eslint/parser` - ^7.0.0\n- `@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin` - ^7.0.0\n- `@types/better-sqlite3` - ^7.6.0\n- `@types/express` - ^4.17.0\n- `supertest` - ^7.0.0\n- `@types/supertest` - ^6.0.0\n- `tsx` - ^4.0.0\n\n**Scripts:**\n- `build` - TypeScript compilation\n- `lint` - ESLint\n- `test` - Run vitest\n- `seed` - Run seed script with tsx\n\n---\n\n### 3. Database Setup (src/db.ts)\n\n**Key Functions:**\n\n1. **`createDatabase(path?: string)`** - Creates a SQLite database\n   - Uses in-memory database if no path provided\n   - Enables WAL (Write-Ahead Logging) pragma\n   - Enables foreign keys pragma\n   - Creates `notes` table if it doesn't exist\n\n2. **`seedDatabase(db)`** - Seeds the database with ~50 sample notes\n   - Inserts notes about programming, cooking, travel, science, music, and more\n   - Uses transactions for performance\n   - Tags stored as JSON strings\n\n**Database Schema:**\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS notes (\n  id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\n  title TEXT NOT NULL,\n  body TEXT NOT NULL,\n  tags TEXT DEFAULT '[]',\n  created_at TEXT DEFAULT (datetime('now')),\n  updated_at TEXT DEFAULT (datetime('now'))\n)\n```\n\n**Seed Data Includes 41 Sample Notes:**\n- Programming topics: TypeScript, Python, Rust, React, Docker, Kubernetes, etc.\n- Database/Performance topics: Database Indexing, SQLite FTS\n- Cooking/Recipes: Pasta, Cookies, Risotto, Thai Cooking, etc.\n- Travel guides: Tokyo, Paris, Southeast Asia, Appalachian Trail, etc.\n- Science topics: Quantum Computing, Solar System, Machine Learning, etc.\n- Music: Jazz History, Classical Music, Guitar Learning, etc.\n- Health topics: Mediterranean Diet, Yoga, Sleep, Meditation, etc.\n- And more...\n\n---\n\n### 4. Data Models (src/models.ts)\n\n**Interfaces:**\n\n```typescript\ninterface Note {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n  body: string;\n  tags: string;          // JSON array as string\n  created_at: string;\n  updated_at: string;\n}\n\ninterface NoteInput {\n  title: string;\n  body: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n}\n\ninterface SearchResult {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n  snippet: string;       // Contains <mark> tags\n  rank: number;\n}\n\ninterface SuggestResult {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. Routes (src/routes.ts)\n\n**Existing CRUD Endpoints (implemented):**\n\n1. **GET /notes** - List all notes\n   - Optional query parameter `?tag=<tag>` for tag filtering\n   - Uses `json_each()` for tag filtering\n   - Returns notes ordered by `created_at DESC`\n\n2. **GET /notes/:id** - Get single note by ID\n   - Returns 404 if not found\n\n3. **POST /notes** - Create new note\n   - Required: `title`, `body`\n   - Optional: `tags` (array)\n   - Validates title and body are not empty\n   - Returns 201 status\n   - Tags stored as JSON string\n\n4. **PUT /notes/:id** - Update note\n   - Partial updates supported\n   - Updates `updated_at` timestamp\n   - Returns 404 if not found\n\n5. **DELETE /notes/:id** - Delete note\n   - Returns 204 status\n   - Returns 404 if not found\n\n**Missing Endpoints (to be implemented):**\n- `GET /notes/search?q=<query>` - Full-text search with pagination\n- `GET /notes/search/suggest?q=<prefix>` - Autocomplete suggestions\n\n---\n\n### 6. Error Handling (src/errors.ts)\n\n**Custom Error Classes:**\n\n1. **`NotFoundError`** - 404 status code\n   - Default message: \"Resource not found\"\n\n2. **`ValidationError`** - 400 status code\n   - Default message: \"Validation failed\"\n\n**Error Handler Middleware:**\n- Catches `NotFoundError` and returns 404\n- Catches `ValidationError` and returns 400\n- Generic errors return 500 with \"Internal server error\"\n- Logs generic errors to console\n\n---\n\n### 7. Server Setup (src/server.ts)\n\n**Key Exports:**\n\n1. **`createApp(dbPath?: string): App`**\n   - Creates Express app with database\n   - Sets up JSON middleware\n   - Mounts routes\n   - Attaches error handler\n\n2. **`createSeededApp(dbPath?: string): App`**\n   - Creates app and seeds it with sample data\n   - Used for testing\n\n**App Interface:**\n```typescript\ninterface App {\n  app: express.Express;\n  db: Database.Database;\n}\n```\n\n**Server Startup:**\n- Starts on port from `process.env.PORT` or 3000\n- Runs automatically if executed directly\n\n---\n\n### 8. Seed Script (src/seed.ts)\n\n**Functionality:**\n- Accepts database path as CLI argument (defaults to `'notes.db'`)\n- Creates database and seeds it\n- Logs seed progress and total count\n- Closes database after completion\n\n**CLI Usage:**\n```bash\nnpm run seed [database-path]\n# Example: npm run seed notes.db\n```\n\n---\n\n### 9. Test Files\n